<item>
            <title>[JDK-8320525] G1: G1UpdateRemSetTrackingBeforeRebuild::distribute_marked_bytes accesses partially unloaded klass</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8320525</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>For debug purposes G1UpdateRemSetTrackingBeforeRebuild::distribute_marked_bytes() accesses the size of the humongous object it is currently processing.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
In case of marked_bytes == 0, the object is actually dead, and the code should not access the klass any more.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This currently does not matter because we purge the metaspace for unloaded classes after this code, but still this is ugly.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Makes code that moves the purging before G1UpdateRemSetTrackingBeforeRebuild crash on some platforms (linux-x86).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
